properties.Name: DrillHole
properties.Description:
A  hole or passage made by a drill for exploratory purposes

BOREHOLE A hole drilled in the material to be blasted, for the purpose of containing an explosive charge, also called BLASTHOLE or DRILL HOLE.

DRILL HOLE A hole drilled in the material to be blasted for the purpose of containing an explosive charge, also called BLASTHOLE or BOREHOLE.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a drill hole.

Columns.Name: MineId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a mine.

Columns.Name: LocationId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Location.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleStartTimestamp
Columns.Description: The period start timestamp of the associated drill hole depth.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleEndTimestamp
Columns.Description: The period end timestamp of the associated drill hole depth.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleElevationRelativeToSurfaceLocationMeters
Columns.Description: The actual elevation of the drill hole relative to the drill hole surface location.

Columns.Name: DrillingMethodTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a drilling method type.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleBurdenTons
Columns.Description: The total amount of material to be blasted by a given hole, usually measured in cubic yards or tons.

Columns.Name: DrillHolePlannedDepthMeters
Columns.Description: The planned depth of the drill hole in meters.

Columns.Name: HoleDiameterCm
Columns.Description: The cross-sectional width of the borehole in cm.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleWaterLevelMeters
Columns.Description: The water level of the drill hole in meters.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleMaximumDepthMeters
Columns.Description: The maximum depth of the drill hole in meters.

Columns.Name: DrillHoleNote
Columns.Description: A note, comment or additional information regarding the drill hole.
